1023
01:35:51,954 --> 01:35:53,314
[SPEAKER_19]: Yeah, thank you, Mr. Chairman.

1024
01:35:53,374 --> 01:35:56,615
[SPEAKER_19]: So just a couple of things for the board to consider.

1025
01:35:57,367 --> 01:36:01,592
[SPEAKER_19]: I don't oppose or support the applicant in any way.

1026
01:36:03,334 --> 01:36:07,538
[SPEAKER_19]: Most cities and towns have a corner clearance requirement and residential zones.

1027
01:36:07,558 --> 01:36:09,500
[SPEAKER_19]: You won't see the same thing in commercial zones.

1028
01:36:09,540 --> 01:36:11,422
[SPEAKER_19]: And the reason being is that

1029
01:36:12,734 --> 01:36:23,325
[SPEAKER_19]: you know, residential neighborhoods are more prone to people kind of jumping forth on stop signs and people are, you know, there's more local traffic.

1030
01:36:23,405 --> 01:36:34,336
[SPEAKER_19]: And so most cities and towns have a 30-foot corner clearance requirement for the purpose of traffic safety in residential neighborhoods, which

1031
01:36:35,556 --> 01:36:40,597
[SPEAKER_19]: is more likely to have an accident when there's not a traffic light.

1032
01:36:40,717 --> 01:36:43,718
[SPEAKER_19]: So that's kind of the origin of the whole thing.

1033
01:36:43,738 --> 01:36:54,341
[SPEAKER_19]: I think it's not unreasonable to have, I don't think that the applicant would need to go through the requirements of having a survey done, but

1034
01:36:55,458 --> 01:37:08,222
[SPEAKER_19]: But clearly here, if you can't even visualize what the obstruction in the corner is, because I have a truck that's six foot high and I'm so far above traffic I can see over a six foot fence, literally.

1035
01:37:09,282 --> 01:37:12,483
[SPEAKER_19]: But people who drive things like Teslas and so forth,

1036
01:37:13,453 --> 01:37:17,396
[SPEAKER_19]: people that are low to the ground or with compact cars, you don't have that same visibility.

1037
01:37:17,436 --> 01:37:24,781
[SPEAKER_19]: The reason why the 30 inches is there or the ability to be able to bring that fence back.

1038
01:37:24,841 --> 01:37:36,450
[SPEAKER_19]: There's nothing here that would disallow the owner to have a four-foot fence provided that they met where the two corners of the straight parallel line intersect.

1039
01:37:37,109 --> 01:37:38,250
[SPEAKER_19]: that's where it's measured.

1040
01:37:38,370 --> 01:37:44,572
[SPEAKER_19]: So I know that the applicant was talking about it reading a couple of different ways or you can read it where whichever way you want.

1041
01:37:44,912 --> 01:37:45,693
[SPEAKER_19]: That's not the case.

1042
01:37:45,733 --> 01:37:54,217
[SPEAKER_19]: The case is that the two parallel points of the outside corner of the curb line is where that goes.

1043
01:37:54,417 --> 01:37:54,777
[SPEAKER_19]: And so

1044
01:37:56,557 --> 01:38:00,239
[SPEAKER_19]: I think that it wouldn't be unreasonable to have the applicant go back.

1045
01:38:00,299 --> 01:38:04,360
[SPEAKER_19]: And we have a really good GIS tool that should be able to spell this out.

1046
01:38:05,020 --> 01:38:09,642
[SPEAKER_19]: I don't think that the board should approve this without some kind of plan.

1047
01:38:10,262 --> 01:38:16,004
[SPEAKER_19]: And I would just implore you to take, certainly this is a serious matter.

1048
01:38:16,044 --> 01:38:18,184
[SPEAKER_19]: It's not a variance that should be granted.

1049
01:38:18,544 --> 01:38:21,545
[SPEAKER_19]: It's just simply, it's a traffic violation.

1050
01:38:23,766 --> 01:38:25,907
[SPEAKER_19]: And every city and town has the same thing.

1051
01:38:26,127 --> 01:38:33,008
[SPEAKER_19]: And normally, and sometimes when bushes get overgrown, the DPW will come and cut them down for you.

1052
01:38:33,148 --> 01:38:35,749
[SPEAKER_19]: So, you know, this is observed statewide.

1053
01:38:36,569 --> 01:38:38,990
[SPEAKER_19]: It is a kind of a home rule here in New England.

1054
01:38:39,130 --> 01:38:50,653
[SPEAKER_19]: And I would just perhaps maybe have the applicant go back and do a little homework and present to this board next month on how this wouldn't be detrimental or dangerous to the to the intersection.

1055
01:38:51,033 --> 01:38:51,213
[SPEAKER_19]: Thank you.

1056
01:38:52,109 --> 01:38:53,130
[SPEAKER_19]: Thank you, Commissioner.

1057
