[SPEAKER_10]: Does anyone see anything?

1061
01:39:13,942 --> 01:39:15,223
[SPEAKER_08]: Yes, we can see it.

1062
01:39:15,484 --> 01:39:15,744
[SPEAKER_10]: Okay.

1063
01:39:16,024 --> 01:39:16,265
[SPEAKER_10]: Yeah.

1064
01:39:16,745 --> 01:39:27,297
[SPEAKER_10]: So am I correctly understanding that these posts here are the partially constructed fence that was stopped that needs the relief?

1065
01:39:27,757 --> 01:39:28,198
[SPEAKER_10]: Is that right?

1066
01:39:29,159 --> 01:39:29,319
[SPEAKER_10]: Yep.

1067
01:39:30,240 --> 01:39:30,400
[SPEAKER_10]: Yes.

1068
01:39:32,134 --> 01:39:49,524
[SPEAKER_10]: And so, Commissioner Forty, at what point in this view, approximately, of course, I'm not expecting an exact measurement, could something of this height extend by right before it starts to run into this corner requirement here?

1069
01:39:49,544 --> 01:39:54,587
[SPEAKER_19]: Yeah, so essentially, Mr. Chairman, the second post in from the very corner,

1070
01:39:56,170 --> 01:40:17,146
[SPEAKER_19]: pretty much parallel measure to the other side would probably not violate the requirements of the ordinance, nor would it have brought the attention of my staff, which I understand had stopped this, which was a good thing because rather than take something down, you know, there are alternatives to this.

1071
01:40:17,687 --> 01:40:18,067
[SPEAKER_19]: I've seen

1072
01:40:18,705 --> 01:40:29,946
[SPEAKER_19]: Things like granite posts with with short rails to give it kind of an old fashioned farm house look type thing, you know that there's other things that can be done here besides a variance.

1073
01:40:31,574 --> 01:40:35,979
[SPEAKER_19]: I would think that, you know, obviously, there has to be some kind of hardship here.

1074
01:40:37,220 --> 01:40:43,928
[SPEAKER_19]: And I just, you know, I don't see that the applicant has provided any hardship here.

1075
01:40:44,088 --> 01:40:49,595
[SPEAKER_19]: And the detriment to the neighborhood is that if you allow it here, you may have to allow it in other corners and

1076
01:40:50,653 --> 01:40:52,995
[SPEAKER_19]: I just don't think it's a good precedent to start.

1077
01:40:53,096 --> 01:41:01,923
[SPEAKER_19]: I think that the yard's big enough where accommodations could be made to at least put it back to a point at which it's not going to be an obstruction, you know.

1078
01:41:01,943 --> 01:41:06,647
[SPEAKER_19]: So, you know, I think allowing this fence to go right out to the corner could be an obstruction.

1079
01:41:07,047 --> 01:41:12,251
[SPEAKER_19]: I mean, it does help that it's an open picket fence, and I don't see that that's, you know,

1080
01:41:13,871 --> 01:41:16,472
[SPEAKER_19]: Obviously, that's not a big problem.

1081
01:41:17,313 --> 01:41:23,515
[SPEAKER_19]: You do have some visibility there with a transparent or semi-transparent fence.

1082
01:41:23,615 --> 01:41:36,461
[SPEAKER_19]: But here, again, I would just caution the board that you may set a precedence here where everybody has a core lot and everybody's going to want to take the maximum amount of their property.

1083
01:41:36,501 --> 01:41:41,763
[SPEAKER_19]: I could see, obviously, the need for some privacy or some isolation, and there's certainly nothing wrong with that.

1084
01:41:43,266 --> 01:41:48,661
[SPEAKER_19]: Again, as I say, the ordinance is there for a reason, and the reason here is public safety.

1085
01:41:50,184 --> 01:41:51,485
[SPEAKER_19]: All right.

1086
01:41:52,025 --> 01:41:56,248
[SPEAKER_10]: Yeah, so for the applicant, there's a few options here.

1087
01:41:56,428 --> 01:42:00,051
[SPEAKER_10]: So if you'd like, we can continue the hearing.

1088
01:42:00,071 --> 01:42:01,352
[SPEAKER_10]: We can discuss this.

1089
01:42:01,432 --> 01:42:04,074
[SPEAKER_10]: The board can ask clarifying questions.

1090
01:42:04,134 --> 01:42:08,097
[SPEAKER_10]: We'll open for public comment, and then the board will deliberate.

1091
01:42:08,898 --> 01:42:15,903
[SPEAKER_10]: The standard for a variance is that the board needs to be able to establish that due to

1092
01:42:17,167 --> 01:42:38,120
[SPEAKER_10]: the shape, topography, or soil conditions of the lot or structure prior to the beginning of the construction, that's the source of the hardship that requires an exception to the four-foot rule for a corner fence.

1093
01:42:39,220 --> 01:42:45,444
[SPEAKER_10]: So if you'd like, we can proceed down that path, and the board could make a decision tonight.

1094
01:42:47,773 --> 01:42:52,482
[SPEAKER_10]: Like I was alluding to the materials you provided.

1095
01:42:53,825 --> 01:42:58,974
[SPEAKER_10]: Aren't as descriptive as the board is accustomed to, but perhaps the board could.

1096
01:43:01,006 --> 01:43:08,909
[SPEAKER_10]: utilize your written description, your verbal descriptions and some images like this to reach the right conclusion.

1097
01:43:10,089 --> 01:43:21,234
[SPEAKER_10]: You also could request to continue this matter to a future hearing and provide some additional details just to help the board make its decision.

1098
01:43:21,254 --> 01:43:22,635
[SPEAKER_10]: Or you could

1099
01:43:24,160 --> 01:43:36,488
[SPEAKER_10]: try to re-engage with the building department and identify a solution that achieves the spirit of what you were trying to accomplish that could be done by right.

1100
01:43:36,568 --> 01:43:39,590
[SPEAKER_10]: So those are the three options as I see them.

1101
01:43:41,531 --> 01:43:47,915
[SPEAKER_10]: So yeah, happy to discuss further, happy to clarify anything, but please let me know your preference.

1102
01:43:47,935 --> 01:43:52,938
[SPEAKER_02]: What would you like me to do?

1103
01:43:59,233 --> 01:44:07,757
[SPEAKER_03]: I mean, yeah, I mean, if you feel I need more than that, I mean, I guess I can try to put something together.

1104
01:44:09,958 --> 01:44:18,623
[SPEAKER_03]: I guess, I mean, I'd like to continue with it and have a vote, but I mean, if you feel like you need more, you know, I mean, yeah, I mean, so what,

1105
01:44:23,963 --> 01:44:35,845
[SPEAKER_03]: when we were brought it to the attention, we were, you know, figured that, you know, if we want to bring it to the corner a lot, if we have to diagonal something, we want to be told what we can do here.

1106
